    "discriminators": [
     "A drawer is a two-part gesture: a low-crest friction glide (the slide) terminated by an impact (the stop or the close). Energy mid-file, then a transient — that is what separates any DRWR from a plain IMPACT subcategory, and the short travel separates it from DOORSlid, which runs for seconds.",
     "Metal is the material axis: a toolbox or filing drawer rings and rattles after it stops (decay_time_seconds_60db ~0.5 s, high inharmonicity), where DRWRWood thuds dead in ~0.1 s. Ball-bearing slides also add a bright, gritty, high-centroid rumble that wood runners lack."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "DRWRWood",
     "DRWRPlas",
     "DOORMetl"
    ]
   }
